A  Kano based Chinese firm Lee Group has partnered the Kano state government in fumigating some public places on Saturday as part of the preventive measures against the COVID 19 pandemic.The exercise which the Kano state governor Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje led other members of his council and the executives of the Lee Group was marked at the government house and Al’s Muhammad Wase specialist hospital in Nasssarawa GRA  of the state. It coincided with the monthly sanitation exercise which is observed every last Saturday of the month and the coy deployed a fire truck fully equipped with fumigants that will clean the most sensitive public places. The governor said the state ministry of environment requested the support of the company which has always helped the people of Kano an they readily offered to work for the benefit of citizens. He further said the closure of the state from other interstate visitors was to safeguard the people and to ensure control adding that only essential items like food and medicine would be allowed entry.